## ‚úÖ Summary

Ethical hacking is a structured, authorized approach to testing security‚Äîemploying the same tools and tactics as hackers, but ethically and legally. It helps organizations stay ahead of threats by uncovering vulnerabilities before they're exploited. From planning and reconnaissance to exploitation and reporting, ethical hacking offers a disciplined methodology to bolster defenses across all levels of infrastructure.


